<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-14-0745 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Committee have conducted an enquiry into the European Community'spolicy for future use of alternative energy sources, taking as a startingpoint the 'Draft recommendation on developing the exploitation of renewableenergy sources in the Community' presented by the Commission to the Councilin October 1987. The Committee considered the following renewable energysources - solar energy (thermal), solar energy (photovoltaic), biomassand energy from waste, geothermal energy, wind energy, tidal power andwave power. This report summarises the provisions in the Commission'sproposals, discusses in turn each of the alternative energy sources onwhich the Committee have received evidence and outlines some of the generalissues raised including economic considerations, the role of the UK Governmentin developing renewables, privatisation and environmental considerations.Finally, the opinions of the Committee on each of the renewable energysources are presented.</TEXT></DOC>